simplesect.para: Efficienty can be improved by writing p2 = A*(B*(C*p1))) instead of p2=A*B*C*p1

simplesect.title: PROPOSED NAMING CONVENTION FOR FRAME-like OBJECTS

para.verbatim: * A naming convention of objects of the type defined in this file : * (1) Frame : F... * Rotation : R ... * (2) Twist : T ... * Wrench : W ... * Vector : V ... * This prefix is followed by : * for category (1) : * F_A_B : w.r.t. frame A, frame B expressed * ( each column of F_A_B corresponds to an axis of B, * expressed w.r.t. frame A ) * in mathematical convention : * A * F_A_B == F * B * * for category (2) : * V_B : a vector expressed w.r.t. frame B * * This can also be prepended by a name : * e.g. : temporaryV_B * * With this convention one can write : * * F_A_B = F_B_A.Inverse(); * F_A_C = F_A_B * F_B_C; * V_B = F_B_C * V_C; // both translation and rotation * V_B = R_B_C * V_C; // only rotation *

simplesect.title: CONVENTIONS FOR WHEN USED WITH ROBOTS :

para.verbatim: * world : represents the frame ([1 0 0,0 1 0,0 0 1],[0 0 0]') * mp : represents mounting plate of a robot * (i.e. everything before MP is constructed by robot manufacturer * everything after MP is tool ) * tf : represents task frame of a robot * (i.e. frame in which motion and force control is expressed) * sf : represents sensor frame of a robot * (i.e. frame at which the forces measured by the force sensor * are expressed ) * * Frame F_world_mp=...; * Frame F_mp_sf(..) * Frame F_mp_tf(,.) * * Wrench are measured in sensor frame SF, so one could write : * Wrench_tf = F_mp_tf.Inverse()* ( F_mp_sf * Wrench_sf ); *

simplesect.title: CONVENTIONS REGARDING UNITS :
simplesect.para: Any consistent series of units can be used, e.g. N,mm,Nmm,..mm/sec

simplesect.title: Twist and Wrench transformations
simplesect.para: 3 different types of transformations do exist for the twists and wrenches.

para.verbatim: * 1) Frame * Twist or Frame * Wrench : * this transforms both the velocity/force reference point * and the basis to which the twist/wrench are expressed. * 2) Rotation * Twist or Rotation * Wrench : * this transforms the basis to which the twist/wrench are * expressed, but leaves the reference point intact. * 3) Twist.RefPoint(v_base_AB) or Wrench.RefPoint(v_base_AB) * this transforms only the reference point. v is expressed * in the same base as the twist/wrench and points from the * old reference point to the new reference point. *

simplesect.title: Spatial cross products
simplesect.para: Let m be a 6D motion vector (Twist) and f be a 6D force vector (Wrench) attached to a rigid body moving with a certain velocity v (Twist). Then * 1) m_dot = v cross m or Twist=Twist*Twist * 2) f_dot = v cross f or Wrench=Twist*Wrench *

simplesect.title: Complexity
simplesect.para: Sometimes the amount of work is given in the documentation e.g. 6M+3A means 6 multiplications and 3 additions.
Erwin Aertbelien, Div. PMA, Dep. of Mech. Eng., K.U.Leuven
